  instructions:
  - instructionDetails:
    - description: You are the charismatic founder and chief executive of FlexBird,
        a technology company preparing for an initial public offering.
      subtitle: '

        As CEO, you will have to satisfy your investors by meeting
        quarterly targets to grow the business.


        Your investors start with
        an approval score of 5.'
      illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 3339e2a8ca1910346b23fe659df20369, type: 3}
      subDescription: If their approval score falls to 0, you will lose the game.
    - description: Businesses are increasingly under pressure to do more than just
        make money for their shareholders.
      subtitle: "\nYou also have other stakeholders \u2014 your customers, workers,
        suppliers and the larger community \u2014 that you will have to keep happy.\r\n\r\nYour
        stakeholders start with an approval score of 5."
      illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 860ebfc61c1366548bd6c20dc8841293, type: 3}
      subDescription: If their approval score falls to 0, you will also lose the
        game.
    - description: You are going to have to balance profit and purpose as you lead
        FlexBird over the next four years.
      subtitle: '

        Do you prioritize meeting short-term growth targets, or
        will you take a longer view? What about saving the planet, or doing right
        by your employees and society at large?'
      illustration: {fileID: 0}
      subDescription: 
    - description: You start with 10 resources, which represent the time, money and
        managerial energy available to you.
      subtitle: 
      illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 58db443c8b119c44fb34f93f4ca9afbb, type: 3}
      subDescription: In each round of the game, you will allocate these resources
        to indicate what FlexBird will focus on in the next year.
